    <!-- Header -->
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="intro-text">
                <div class="intro-lead-in">Welcome To Kuwelisa</div><br>
                <a href="#services" class="page-scroll btn btn-xl">Log In</a><br><br>
                <a href="#contact" class="page-scroll btn btn-xl">Learn About Our Mission</a><br><br>
                <a href="sign_up" class="page-scroll btn btn-xl">Sign Up</a>

            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

     <section id="services">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                    <h2 class="section-heading">Log In</h2>
                </div>
            </div>
              <div class="row", align='center'>

            <%= simple_form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => session_path(resource_name), :html => {:class => 'form-horizontal' }) do |f| %>
                <%= devise_error_messages! %>

                <div class="col-lg-offset-4 col-lg-4 col-md-offset-3 col-md-6 col-sm-offset-3 col-sm-6 col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10">
        
                <div class="field">
                  <%= f.input :phone, placeholder: "Phone number" %><br />
                </div>

                <div class="field">
                  <%= f.input :password, placeholder: "Password" %><br />
                </div>

                <% if devise_mapping.rememberable? -%>
                  <div class="field">
                    <%= f.check_box :remember_me %>
                    <%= f.label :remember_me %>
                  </div>
                <% end -%>

                <div class="actions">
                  <%= f.button :submit, "Log in" %>
                </div>
            <% end %>

          <%= render "devise/shared/links" %>

       
      </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <!-- Services Section -->
   <section id="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                    <h2 class="section-heading">Our Mission</h2>
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row text-center">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                        <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary" style="color: #ccff99"></i>
                        <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-stack-1x fa-inverse" style="color: #003333"></i>
                    </span>
                    <h4 class="service-heading">The Problem</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted">Researchers at the University of Cape Town discovered that transportation is highly inaccessible to individuals of South African townships. Very few are able to afford vehicles and those who aren't do not have access to public transportation. As such, individuals are unable to leave the township to fulfill needs such as hospital care, food, and more.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                        <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary" style="color: #ccff99"></i>
                        <i class="fa fa-car fa-stack-1x fa-inverse" style="color: #003333"></i>
                    </span>
                    <h4 class="service-heading">The Solution</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted">Crowdsourcing is a very common solution to problems in the developed world, but it has yet to make an impact in Cape Town. Kuwelisa aims to bring ride sharing to the townships of South Africa in order to meet the needs of such individuals.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                        <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary" style="color: #ccff99"></i>
                        <i class="fa fa-info fa-stack-1x fa-inverse" style="color: #003333"></i>
                    </span>
                    <h4 class="service-heading">How It Works</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted">Users are given the option of creating trips as drivers or signing up for existing trips as passengers. This app enables individuals with cars to split gas money, make friends, and contribute to the community. On the other hand, it allows those without vehicles to connect with resources existing within the township.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Services Section -->
   
  








                